1. The study involves different styles of nursing.
2. The study has a study group and a control group.
3. There are at least five factors being measured in the study.
4. The scores of the first four factors were significantly lower in the study group than in the control group.
5. The difference in scores of the first four factors between the two groups is statistically significant (P<0.01).
6. The score of the cover factor was not significantly different between the study group and the control group.
7. The difference in the score of the cover factor between the two groups is not statistically significant (P>0.05).
